cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for enhancing supervised learning using Monte Carlo dropout to detect and diagnose incipient faults in buildings. This involves the use of deep neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the analysis of data from buildings, which could fall under the categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
